main event: A bright, glowing object was observed in the sky for around 2 minutes over Wall, Michigan on September 6, 1956.
interesting points: The object was circular in shape, measuring an estimated 15-20 feet in diameter, and had a cream to orange color.
The object moved at an estimated speed of 400-500 mph, and performed erratic maneuvers with sudden stops and starts.
The object was tracked on ground radar simultaneously with the visual sighting by a pilot of F-89 jets on an intercept mission.
The report concludes that the sighting was 'possibly aircraft', but notes that the reality of the sighting was indicated by the radar tracking.
The report includes various numerical codes and text that likely describe the status or characteristics of the reported unidentified flying object (UFO).
witnesses: pilot of F-89 jets, ground radar
